comments: Crowder (PHX) extends his left leg into Young's (CHI) path and initiates body contact that affects Young's SQBR.
Satoransky (CHI) swipes forward and brushes Paul's (PHX) front as Paul receives the pass.
Satoransky (CHI) delivers contact to Ayton's (PHX) side during his upward shooting motion.
Williams (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Ayton's (PHX) path and absorbs the contact.
Ayton (PHX) jumps alongside Vucevic's (CHI) path as marginal body contact occurs during Vucevic's upward shooting motoin.
Ayton (PHX) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Ayton (PHX) is slightly late establishing himself in Valentine's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact that occurs as he sets the pick.

Ayton (PHX) swipes forward and marginal contact occurs with Valentine's (CHI) head/neck area during rebounding. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Valentine (CHI) has his arm around Ayton's (PHX) upper half and quickly releases as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Vucevic (CHI) grasps and then quickly releases Crowder's (PHX) right arm as the entry pass is made.
Ayton (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the body contact made with Young (CHI) during the layup attempt.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Williams' (CHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Vucevic (CHI) maintains a rested forearm on Booker's (PHX) side and marginal contact occurs after Booker's gather.
Saric (PHX) and Young (CHI) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Young (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Ayton's (PHX) path and absorbs the contact.
Saric (PHX) has his hand rested on Valentine's (CHI) side during the drive and cleanly dislodges Saric of the ball before any incidental contact occurs.
Valentine (CHI) swipes forward and marginal contact occurs with Paul's (PHX) front as he gains control of the loose ball.
In transition, Williams (PHX) moves into and commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
Ayton (PHX) places his forearm to Young's (CHI) front and marginal contact occurs as Young stops his forward momentum.
Williams (CHI) commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
Saric (PHX) extends his hand forward toward Young's (CHI) front and marginal contact occurs during Young's drive.
Saric (PHX) rests his hand on Young's (CHI) side and marginal contact occurs during Young's driving shot attempt.
